The President's State of the Union Address in 2015 focused on the progress made in the past fifteen years, including overcoming the challenges of terrorism, wars, and recession. The President emphasized the need to choose an economy that benefits everyone and the success of middle-class economics. He highlighted the importance of adapting to economic change and providing opportunities for all citizens. The President also discussed the need for smarter American leadership, combining military power with diplomacy and coalition building. He mentioned the efforts to stop ISIL's advance in Iraq and Syria and called on Congress to authorize the use of force against the terrorist group. Additionally, the President addressed the threat of cyber-attacks and the need for legislation to protect against them.